# Visualization Guide for JsonSlidesMaker

This guide shows you how to create stunning visualizations in your presentations using AI-generated images, diagrams, and charts.

## Quick Overview

JsonSlidesMaker supports 4 types of visualizations:
1. **AI Images (DALL-E)** - Generate professional images from text descriptions
2. **Mermaid Diagrams** - Create flowcharts, sequences, and other diagrams  
3. **Data Charts** - Generate bar, line, pie charts from your data
4. **Placeholder Images** - Quick placeholder images with custom text

## 1. AI-Generated Images (DALL-E)

### Basic Usage
```json
{
  "visualizations": [
    {
      "type": "ai_image",
      "data": {
        "prompt": "Modern office space with team collaboration, bright natural lighting, professional photography style",
        "size": "1024x1024"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Requirements
- Set environment variable: `export OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key`
- Install OpenAI: `pip install openai`

### Effective Prompts

**For Business Presentations:**
```json
{
  "prompt": "Professional business team analyzing data on holographic displays, futuristic office, blue and white color scheme, wide angle shot"
}
```

**For Product Showcases:**
```json
{
  "prompt": "Sleek mobile app interface showing dashboard with charts and metrics, floating iPhone mockup, gradient background, 3D render"
}
```

**For Architecture Diagrams:**
```json
{
  "prompt": "Cloud infrastructure visualization with interconnected servers and data flows, isometric style, tech blue colors, white background"
}
```

### Pro Tips for AI Images
- **Specify style**: "photography", "illustration", "3D render", "watercolor"
- **Include lighting**: "soft lighting", "dramatic shadows", "golden hour"
- **Define composition**: "close-up", "wide angle", "aerial view", "centered"
- **Add mood**: "professional", "inspiring", "modern", "minimalist"

### Complete Example
```json
{
  "layout": {
    "type": "exact",
    "name": "21_One Column and an Image On the Right"
  },
  "content": {
    "title": "**Digital Transformation Vision**",
    "body": [
      "Transform your business with cutting-edge technology:",
      "‚Ä¢ Cloud-native architecture",
      "‚Ä¢ AI-powered insights",
      "‚Ä¢ Real-time analytics"
    ],
    "visualizations": [
      {
        "type": "ai_image",
        "data": {
          "prompt": "Futuristic command center with multiple screens showing real-time data analytics, team of diverse professionals, cinematic lighting, ultra modern design",
          "size": "1024x1024"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## 2. Mermaid Diagrams

### Flowcharts
```json
{
  "visualizations": [
    {
      "type": "mermaid",
      "data": {
        "code": "graph TD\n    A[Customer Request] --> B{Valid?}\n    B -->|Yes| C[Process Order]\n    B -->|No| D[Return Error]\n    C --> E[Ship Product]\n    E --> F[Send Confirmation]\n    style A fill:#e3f2fd\n    style F fill:#c8e6c9"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Sequence Diagrams
```json
{
  "type": "mermaid",
  "data": {
    "code": "sequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant Frontend\n    participant API\n    participant Database\n    User->>Frontend: Login Request\n    Frontend->>API: POST /auth/login\n    API->>Database: Verify Credentials\n    Database-->>API: User Data\n    API-->>Frontend: JWT Token\n    Frontend-->>User: Dashboard"
  }
}
```

### Process Flow
```json
{
  "type": "mermaid",
  "data": {
    "code": "graph LR\n    A[Requirements] --> B[Design]\n    B --> C[Development]\n    C --> D[Testing]\n    D --> E{Pass?}\n    E -->|Yes| F[Deploy]\n    E -->|No| C\n    F --> G[Monitor]\n    G --> H[Feedback]\n    H --> A"
  }
}
```

### Organization Chart
```json
{
  "type": "mermaid",
  "data": {
    "code": "graph TD\n    CEO[CEO]\n    CEO --> CTO[CTO]\n    CEO --> CFO[CFO]\n    CEO --> CMO[CMO]\n    CTO --> DEV[Dev Team]\n    CTO --> OPS[Operations]\n    CFO --> ACC[Accounting]\n    CFO --> FIN[Finance]\n    CMO --> SALES[Sales]\n    CMO --> MARK[Marketing]"
  }
}
```

### State Diagram
```json
{
  "type": "mermaid",
  "data": {
    "code": "stateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Draft\n    Draft --> Review\n    Review --> Approved\n    Review --> Rejected\n    Rejected --> Draft\n    Approved --> Published\n    Published --> [*]"
  }
}
```

## 3. Data Charts

### Bar Chart
```json
{
  "visualizations": [
    {
      "type": "bar",
      "data": {
        "values": [45, 38, 52, 41, 55, 48],
        "labels": ["Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun"],
        "title": "Monthly Revenue ($M)",
        "x_label": "Month",
        "y_label": "Revenue"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Line Chart (Trends)
```json
{
  "type": "line",
  "data": {
    "values": [100, 120, 115, 140, 155, 180, 195, 220],
    "labels": ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4", "Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4"],
    "title": "User Growth Over Time",
    "x_label": "Quarter",
    "y_label": "Users (thousands)"
  }
}
```

### Pie Chart (Distribution)
```json
{
  "type": "pie",
  "data": {
    "values": [35, 25, 20, 15, 5],
    "labels": ["Enterprise", "SMB", "Startup", "Individual", "Other"],
    "title": "Customer Segments"
  }
}
```

### Multi-Series Data (Advanced)
```json
{
  "type": "bar",
  "data": {
    "categories": ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4"],
    "series": [
      {
        "name": "Product A",
        "values": [30, 35, 32, 38]
      },
      {
        "name": "Product B", 
        "values": [25, 28, 30, 35]
      }
    ],
    "title": "Product Comparison",
    "x_label": "Quarter",
    "y_label": "Sales ($M)"
  }
}
```

## 4. Placeholder Images

Quick placeholders when you need something fast:

```json
{
  "visualizations": [
    {
      "type": "placeholder",
      "data": {
        "text": "Analytics Dashboard",
        "category": "dashboard",
        "style": {
          "background": "#1976d2",
          "text_color": "#ffffff",
          "font_size": 36
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Categories
- `chart` - Chart-style placeholder
- `dashboard` - Dashboard mockup
- `diagram` - Diagram placeholder
- `flowchart` - Flowchart style
- `photo` - Photo placeholder

## Real-World Examples

### Sales Presentation
```json
{
  "slides": [
    {
      "layout": {
        "type": "exact",
        "name": "21_One Column and an Image On the Right"
      },
      "content": {
        "title": "**Q4 Sales Performance**",
        "body": [
          "Record-breaking quarter:",
          "‚Ä¢ Total Revenue: $52M",
