# BEIT Template Layout Guide

This guide describes all available layouts in the BEIT template (ID: `101cmCr04_J3XlrkI_JEZT6Dadx_KTySyLTVzvyWRbL8`) to help you create effective presentations.

## Available Layouts

### 1. Title Slide (`1_Title Slide`)
**Purpose**: Opening slide, section dividers, or standalone statements  
**Content Support**:
- Title (large, centered)
- Subtitle (smaller, below title)

**Best For**:
- Presentation opening
- Chapter/section dividers
- Key statements or quotes

**Example JSON**:
```json
{
  "layout": {
    "type": "exact",
    "name": "1_Title Slide"
  },
  "content": {
    "title": "**Digital Transformation Strategy**",
    "subtitle": "Building Tomorrow's Infrastructure Today"
  }
}
```

### 2. Section Header (`2_Section Header`)
**Purpose**: Section transitions with visual emphasis  
**Content Support**:
- Title (prominent)
- Background image capability
- Minimal text for impact

**Best For**:
- Major section breaks
- Agenda items
- Visual transitions

**Example JSON**:
```json
{
  "layout": {
    "type": "exact", 
    "name": "2_Section Header"
  },
  "content": {
    "title": "**Phase 1: Assessment**"
  }
}
```

### 3. Title and Content (`4_Title and Content`)
**Purpose**: Standard content slides with title and body text  
**Content Support**:
- Title
- Multiple body text areas
- Bullet points and paragraphs

**Best For**:
- Detailed explanations
- Lists and bullet points
- Standard informational slides

**Example JSON**:
```json
{
  "layout": {
    "type": "exact",
    "name": "4_Title and Content"
  },
  "content": {
    "title": "**Key Benefits**",
    "body": [
      "‚Ä¢ **Increased Efficiency** - 40% faster processing",
      "‚Ä¢ **Cost Reduction** - Save $2M annually",
      "‚Ä¢ **Better User Experience** - 95% satisfaction rate",
      "‚Ä¢ **Scalability** - Handle 10x current load"
    ]
  }
}
```

### 4. Three-Column Table (`7_Three-column table`)
**Purpose**: Structured comparison or categorized information  
**Content Support**:
- Title
- Three column structure
- Table-like layout

**Best For**:
- Feature comparisons
- Timeline presentations
- Categorized information

**Example JSON**:
```json
{
  "layout": {
    "type": "exact",
    "name": "7_Three-column table"
  },
  "content": {
    "title": "**Implementation Timeline**",
    "columns": {
      "left": {
        "type": "text",
        "content": ["**Q1 2024**", "‚Ä¢ Planning", "‚Ä¢ Team Setup", "‚Ä¢ Initial Design"]
      },
      "center": {
        "type": "text", 
        "content": ["**Q2 2024**", "‚Ä¢ Development", "‚Ä¢ Testing", "‚Ä¢ Beta Launch"]
      },
      "right": {
        "type": "text",
        "content": ["**Q3 2024**", "‚Ä¢ Full Launch", "‚Ä¢ Training", "‚Ä¢ Optimization"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 5. Two-Column Layout (`11_Two-column`)
**Purpose**: Side-by-side content comparison or complementary information  
**Content Support**:
- Title
- Two equal columns
- Text or mixed content

**Best For**:
- Pros/cons lists
- Before/after comparisons
- Parallel concepts

**Example JSON**:
```json
{
  "layout": {
    "type": "exact",
    "name": "11_Two-column"
  },
  "content": {
